headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 27 points and eight assists to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 124-117 win against the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards has 27 points and eight assists to lead Timberwolves to 124-117 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — There were differing versions of whether the Atlanta Hawks wanted to call a timeout to set up their final shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray hits 17-footer at buzzer to lift Hawks past Magic, 106-104

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — French phenom Victor Wembanyama called it special to play his first game on the Boston Celtics' famous parquet court.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 24 to lead Celtics past Wembanyama, Spurs 117-98

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 31 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers took advantage of Milwaukee being without superstar Giannis Antetokounmpo to extend their winning streak to a season-best six games by pounding the Bucks 135-95 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 31 points as Cavaliers thrash Giannis-less Bucks 135-95 for 6th win in a row

events.name: Houston Rockets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Bruised and beaten after a rough outing without Jalen Brunson two days earlier, Julius Randle said he told his teammate to get back out on the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 31 points, Brunson has 30 in return to help the Knicks beat the Rockets 109-94

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored a season-high 28 points, RJ Barrett had 26 and the Toronto Raptors never trailed in a 121-97 win over the Miami Heat on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent scores season-high 28 points, Barrett adds 26 as Raptors rout Heat 121-97

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram put an emphatic, crowd-pleasing end to his recent shooting slump.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram gets triple-double, Pelicans set franchise record for 3s with 25 in 132-112 win over Hornets

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis is already an established scorer and rebounder. The Las Angeles Lakers' All-Star center is beginning to show he is developing into an adept passer.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis, Lakers overcome Luka Doncic's triple-double to beat Mavericks, 127-110

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz
Brooklyn Nets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons started feeling better just in time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons hits winner with 0.2 seconds on the clock as Trail Blazers beat Nets 105-103
